{
  "text": "On the basis of the present and previous findings [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] we suggest that shrinkage of DA neurons and reduction of spine density on their post-synaptic elements (i.e. MSN) upon withdrawal from chronic cannabinoid administration might represent a morphological correlate of the functional deficits detected by electrophysiological [CITATION_4] and neurochemical [CITATION_5] means, which may ultimately contribute to negative motivational properties of withdrawal from addictive drugs [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
  "correct_citation": {
